cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper deals with word sense disambiguation in the biomedical domain using supervised learning algorithms and features extracted from the context of an ambiguous word. This topic falls under the natural language processing (NLP) domain, which is covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. Specifically, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as it covers NLP and machine learning methods for text analysis. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as it covers techniques for text classification and information extraction. cs.LG (Machine Learning) covers the use of machine learning algorithms, which are used in this paper. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also possible categories as they cover machine learning and neural network techniques.
